    id: 5281,
    text: 'You are designing an integration between Dataverse and an external application. The external application processes thousands of records per day.\n\nRecord processing volumes vary throughout the day. Extremely high processing volumes may occur and may exceed the Dataverse service protection API limits.\n\nYou need to implement each service protection limit that is enforced.\n\nWhich implementations should you use?\n\nOPTIONS:\nService Protection Limit -> Implementation\n- Number of requests ->\n  1. Number per user over a sliding window of time\n  2. Number per environment over a sliding window of time\n  3. Number per user per 24-hour period\n  4. Number per environment per 24-hour period\n- Combined execution time ->\n  1. Combined time per user over a sliding window of time\n  2. Combined time per user over a fixed window of time\n  3. Combined time per environment over a sliding window of time\n  4. Combined time per environment over a fixed window of time\n- Concurrent requests ->\n  1. Fixed number per user\n  2. Fixed number per tenant\n  3. Fixed number per application\n  4. Fixed number per environment',
    type: 'multiple',
